<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/942.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-14">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Minister of Finance has served written demand on the bankers to
                                answer by June 15 whether or not they will advance 19,000,000 taels
                                more during June; otherwise he will get the money elsewhere. He
                                knows that the bankers cannot answer definitely within the time be
                                has fixed, as they are dependent on the result of the Paris meeting.
                                The ultimatum suggests interference from outside at this end. It is
                                    <pb facs="0254" n="138" xml:id="pg_138"/> reported that Tong has
                                been conferring with the Russians. Possibly Russia prefers to have
                                the Chinese break with the groups here and thereby relieve her of
                                the onus of forcing a rupture in Paris.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>